## Architecture

- **Two repos / two surfaces:** main worker (`inneranimalmedia.com`) vs MCP worker (`mcp.inneranimalmedia.com`). In-app Agent Sam never routes through MCP; see `docs/platform/iam-runtime-architecture-2026-06.md`.
- **Registry truth:** workflow keys, tools, handlers → D1 (`agentsam_workflows`, `agentsam_workflow_handlers`, `agentsam_tools`, …). MCP OAuth `tools/list` reads `agentsam_tools` (`oauth_visible`); do not add `agentsam_mcp_tools` (dropped migration 498). Use `resolveWorkflowFromSurfaceMetadata` — no new `firstActiveWorkflowKeyAmong`.
- **`agentsam_*` prefix:** operational control-plane tables use full name; never invent unprefixed synonyms (`prompt_routes` does not exist).
- **Two DB lanes:** `d1_*` / `env.DB` (D1 only) vs `supabase_*` / Hyperdrive (Postgres only). No Postgres through D1 binding.
- **Workflow executor:** `handler_config_json` from D1; empty config → throw; edges use `from_status`: `success` | `failed` | `any`.
- **Wrangler secrets:** platform only (~fixed set). Per-user keys in D1 `user_secrets` / `user_api_keys` / `mcp_workspace_tokens` — never per-user Wrangler secrets.
- **MCP bearer:** shown once; D1 stores hash only (`generateMcpToken` / `TOKEN_SIGNING_KEY` on worker).

